Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(peeled and cut into 1-inch-thick wedges); mince 1 wedge. Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut into long, thin wedges. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add minced onion and @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until onion is softened and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings) and @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 5.

Meanwhile, toss zucchini and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @sumac{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Broil, tossing halfway through, until lightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

While veggies roast, slice @grilling cheese{8%ounce} into four large pieces (eight pieces for 4 servings).

Place @Za'atar spice{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}. Coat cheese in za'atar, pressing to adhere.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add cheese and cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

Transfer cooked couscous to a large #bowl{}. Stir in tomatoes, lemon zest, half the roasted veggies, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous mixture between plates. Top with grilling cheese and remaining roasted veggies. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.